- Yup. Yeah.

247
00:23:47,054 --> 00:23:50,086
Hey, I wasn't just flapping my lips
about my kid brother and me.

248
00:23:50,446 --> 00:23:54,820
What I figured was if you and Jesse could
gauge our courage and our daring...

249
00:23:54,988 --> 00:23:57,158
...you might just make us
your regular sidekicks.

250
00:23:57,324 --> 00:23:59,462
Your courage and your daring.

251
00:24:00,682 --> 00:24:05,538
I about heard all I want to about sidekicks.
You sound like your damn brother.

252
00:24:05,706 --> 00:24:10,017
Yeah. Well, I'll be square with you,
it's Bob who put me up to it. He's...

253
00:24:10,571 --> 00:24:13,734
He's got plans for the James boys
I can't even get the hang of.

254
00:24:13,899 --> 00:24:15,623
- They're that complicated.
- Yeah?

255
00:24:16,651 --> 00:24:19,202
Well, you can just
get shed of that idea.

256
00:24:19,370 --> 00:24:21,790
Because after tonight,
there'll be no more shenanigans.

257
00:24:22,442 --> 00:24:25,160
You can jot that down in your little diary.

258
00:24:25,322 --> 00:24:29,893
September 7th, 1881, the James Gang
robbed one last train at Blue Cut...

259
00:24:30,057 --> 00:24:32,444
...and gave up their nightriding for good.

260
00:24:38,825 --> 00:24:40,253
Wait.

261
00:24:41,799 --> 00:24:44,219
Well, how are you gonna
make your living?

262
00:24:48,967 --> 00:24:51,270
Maybe I'll sell shoes.

263
00:25:00,679 --> 00:25:02,686
I can't believe I woke up this morning...

264
00:25:02,854 --> 00:25:06,018
...wondering if my daddy
would loan me his overcoat...

265
00:25:06,182 --> 00:25:07,970
...and here it is just past midnight...

266
00:25:08,133 --> 00:25:11,547
...l've already robbed a railroad train
and I'm sitting in a rocking chair...

267
00:25:11,716 --> 00:25:13,855
...chatting with none other
than Jesse James.

268
00:25:14,565 --> 00:25:17,085
Yeah, it's a wonderful world.

269
00:25:25,154 --> 00:25:26,911
What's this?

270
00:25:27,108 --> 00:25:28,733
Oh, yeah.

271
00:25:29,859 --> 00:25:33,753
I was real agitated this morning, so I was
wondering if I would know you or Frank...

272
00:25:33,923 --> 00:25:38,844
...tell you all apart, and so I had
this clipping that described you both.

273
00:25:39,330 --> 00:25:40,988
Want me to read it?

274
00:25:41,571 --> 00:25:42,681
Go on.

275
00:25:42,850 --> 00:25:46,779
Well... I gotta find it. Hold on.

276
00:25:47,651 --> 00:25:49,789
Here. Here.

277
00:25:49,953 --> 00:25:53,912
"Jesse James, the youngest, has a face
as smooth and innocent as a schoolgirl.

278
00:25:54,079 --> 00:25:58,271
The blue eyes, very clear and penetrating,
are never at rest.

279
00:25:58,432 --> 00:26:01,783
His form is tall and graceful
and capable of great endurance...

280
00:26:01,953 --> 00:26:03,327
...and great effort.

281
00:26:03,488 --> 00:26:07,317
Jesse is lighthearted, reckless,
and devil-may-care.

282
00:26:08,318 --> 00:26:11,548
- There's always a smile on his lips..."
- All right, all right, all right.

283
00:26:11,711 --> 00:26:15,355
Well, yeah, then it just... Frank, Frank,
Frank. That's nothing. And then...

284
00:26:27,294 --> 00:26:29,082
You know what I got
right next to my bed?

285
00:26:29,694 --> 00:26:34,549
Is The Train Robbers, or, A Story
of the James Boys by R.W. Stevens.

286
00:26:34,715 --> 00:26:37,532
I mean, many's the night I stayed up...

287
00:26:37,947 --> 00:26:40,021
...with my eyes open
and my mouth open...

288
00:26:40,189 --> 00:26:43,222
...just reading about your escapades
in the Wide Awake Library.

289
00:26:45,275 --> 00:26:46,901
They're all lies, you know.

290
00:26:50,170 --> 00:26:52,058
Yeah, of course they are.

291
00:26:55,197 --> 00:26:58,261
You don't have to keep smoking that
if it's making you bungey.

292
00:27:21,113 --> 00:27:23,447
Alexander Franklin James
would be in Baltimore...

293
00:27:23,608 --> 00:27:27,122
...when he would read of
the assassination of Jesse James.

294
00:27:40,023 --> 00:27:44,430
He had spurned his younger brother
for being peculiar and temperamental.

295
00:27:45,750 --> 00:27:48,880
But once he perceived
that he would never see Jesse again...

296
00:27:49,461 --> 00:27:53,901
...Frank would be wrought-up,
perplexed, despondent.

297
00:28:31,026 --> 00:28:34,158
My brother and me are hardly
on speaking terms these days.

298
00:28:35,506 --> 00:28:37,677
Well, I wasn't gonna mention it.

299
00:28:47,792 --> 00:28:49,166
Are you scared?

300
00:28:49,936 --> 00:28:51,978
No, I'm just surprised a little.

301
00:28:52,145 --> 00:28:54,599
They ain't as succulent as I like,
the devil to clean...

302
00:28:54,768 --> 00:28:57,701
...but if a man skins them
and fries them in garlic and oil...

303
00:28:57,871 --> 00:29:00,621
...mercy, them's good eating.

304
00:29:00,784 --> 00:29:03,980
Well, I never been that hungry.

305
00:29:06,608 --> 00:29:08,615
I give them names.

306
00:29:09,999 --> 00:29:11,340
Such as?

307
00:29:13,934 --> 00:29:16,322
Such as enemies.

308
00:29:17,261 --> 00:29:19,912
I give them names of enemies.

309
00:29:32,142 --> 00:29:35,075
Go tell Wood and Charley
to get their gatherings together.

310
00:29:36,461 --> 00:29:37,955
All right.

311
00:29:39,307 --> 00:29:40,801
Me too?

312
00:29:42,858 --> 00:29:44,747
You can stay.

313
00:29:47,596 --> 00:29:48,576
All right.

314
00:29:54,923 --> 00:29:56,167
Hey.

315
00:29:58,313 --> 00:30:00,899
- What do you want, peckerwood?
- Nothing.

316
00:30:01,066 --> 00:30:03,586
Except to say Jesse wants
you two to gather your parts...

317
00:30:03,754 --> 00:30:06,174
...get on your horses
and get out of town.

318
00:30:06,473 --> 00:30:08,381
And me to stick around.

319
00:30:10,633 --> 00:30:13,600
Well, whoa, I'm his cousin...

320
00:30:13,770 --> 00:30:15,428
...l'll have you know.

321
00:30:15,592 --> 00:30:17,665
My mama's his daddy's sister.

322
00:30:18,024 --> 00:30:20,161
Is that how they described it to you,
Wood?

323
00:30:21,768 --> 00:30:23,807
You better watch your tongue,
young sapling.

324
00:30:23,975 --> 00:30:27,204
Why is it me who's gotta rattle his hocks
out of town and not you, Bunny?

325
00:30:27,366 --> 00:30:29,023
Put your horns away.
If I know Jess...

326
00:30:29,190 --> 00:30:32,288
...there's some real nasty
sad-suzie work's gotta be done...

327
00:30:32,679 --> 00:30:35,427
...and Bob's the ninny that has to do it.

328
00:30:35,591 --> 00:30:37,761
Oh, yeah, I'm sure that's it, Charley.

329
00:30:39,429 --> 00:30:43,936
You only met him 12 hours ago.
He doesn't even know your name.

330
00:30:44,934 --> 00:30:48,251
Wood! You tell your daddy
I'll be in Kentucky in October.

331
00:30:49,604 --> 00:30:51,874
We can hunt some birds together.

332
00:30:52,387 --> 00:30:53,763
All right.

333
00:30:54,501 --> 00:30:57,849
So how come it's Bob who gets to stay?

334
00:31:00,324 --> 00:31:03,193
Bob's gonna move my gear to a house
down the street.

335
00:31:04,196 --> 00:31:05,177
See?

336
00:31:05,923 --> 00:31:08,345
- I don't mind.
- Yeah, well.

337
00:31:08,515 --> 00:31:10,523
Sounds like an adventure.

338
00:31:14,852 --> 00:31:17,917
They moved to 1017 Troost Avenue
at night...

339
00:31:18,083 --> 00:31:22,337
...so that the neighborhood couldn't get
a good look at them or their belongings.

340
00:31:23,969 --> 00:31:26,556
Then Bob thought Jesse
would give him eight hours' sleep...

341
00:31:26,722 --> 00:31:28,991
...and a daydreaming goodbye.

342
00:31:31,842 --> 00:31:34,775
But with a second day
in the Thomas Howard house...

343
00:31:34,945 --> 00:31:36,853
...Bob thought he might never go...

344
00:31:37,695 --> 00:31:41,340
...but might be brought in
as a good-natured cousin to the boy...

345
00:31:42,719 --> 00:31:45,370
...and a gentleman helper to Zee.

346
00:31:48,254 --> 00:31:49,947
He went everywhere with Jesse.

347
00:31:50,112 --> 00:31:52,283
They made trips
to the Topeka Exchange Saloon...

348
00:31:52,446 --> 00:31:56,092
...where Jesse could spend nearly
60 minutes sipping one glass of beer...

349
00:31:56,256 --> 00:31:59,353
...and still complain about feeling tipsy.

350
00:31:59,997 --> 00:32:02,867
Bob would rarely vouchsafe his opinions
as they talked.

351
00:32:03,038 --> 00:32:06,420
If spoken to, he would fidget and grin.

352
00:32:07,134 --> 00:32:11,028
If Jesse palavered with another person,
Bob secretaried their dialogue...

353
00:32:11,198 --> 00:32:14,808
...getting each inflection,
reading every gesture and tic...

354
00:32:14,974 --> 00:32:18,040
...as if he wanted to compose
a biography of the outlaw...

355
00:32:18,206 --> 00:32:21,020
...or as if he were preparing
an impersonation.

356
00:32:36,219 --> 00:32:38,073
Go away.

357
00:32:40,794 --> 00:32:44,372
Used to be couldn't no one sneak up
on Jesse James.

358
00:32:45,658 --> 00:32:47,926
Now you think otherwise?

359
00:32:48,955 --> 00:32:52,019
I ain't never seen you without your guns,
neither.

360
00:33:04,728 --> 00:33:06,964
I can't figure it out.

361
00:33:07,832 --> 00:33:09,902
Do you wanna be like me...

362
00:33:10,326 --> 00:33:11,757
...or do you wanna be me?

363
00:33:17,431 --> 00:33:19,602
I'm just making fun, is all.

364
00:33:22,135 --> 00:33:25,266
Bob was sent away cordially
the next day...

365
00:33:25,431 --> 00:33:26,860
...with a goodbye from Jesse...

366
00:33:27,030 --> 00:33:30,804
...but nothing from Zee
beyond what good manners demanded.

367
00:33:34,229 --> 00:33:36,948
It was 40 miles to his sister's farm
from Kansas City.

368
00:33:38,196 --> 00:33:42,319
And it was well into the afternoon
by the time he arrived there.

369
00:33:43,285 --> 00:33:47,147
Mrs. Martha Bolton rented
the Harbison farm in 1879...

370
00:33:47,318 --> 00:33:49,773
...just after becoming a widow.

371
00:33:50,230 --> 00:33:52,846
And she made a good income
by giving rooms and meals...

372
00:33:53,012 --> 00:33:57,964
...to her brothers Charley, Wilbur and Bob,
and to members of the James Gang...

373
00:33:58,132 --> 00:34:00,519
...who would appear
whenever they needed seclusion.

374
00:34:00,690 --> 00:34:02,317
Dick! You're gonna make her sick!

375
00:34:02,484 --> 00:34:05,331
She's gonna upchuck
if you don't watch out!

376
00:34:05,874 --> 00:34:08,939
Wood Hite had been spurned by Martha
in his affections...

377
00:34:09,105 --> 00:34:11,691
...and his attempt to switch his pursuit
to her daughter...

378
00:34:11,857 --> 00:34:13,681
...was being thwarted by Dick Liddil.

379
00:34:13,842 --> 00:34:17,007
Wait a second, you assured me
that you were not ticklish.

380
00:34:17,170 --> 00:34:18,151
Howdy!

381
00:34:18,321 --> 00:34:20,077
What's going on, now?
What's going on...?

382
00:34:20,241 --> 00:34:22,957
- Howdy!
- Were you fibbing about that?

383
00:34:23,120 --> 00:34:24,844
- No.
- Not at all.

384
00:34:26,321 --> 00:34:27,947
You're not supposed to peek, Dick.

385
00:34:28,112 --> 00:34:30,448
Well, you're just so pretty
I can't help myself.

386
00:34:30,609 --> 00:34:32,997
- You need to be warning him about that.
- Howdy.

387
00:34:33,168 --> 00:34:36,942
Worry about the field instead,
might be able to worry about the work...

388
00:34:37,104 --> 00:34:38,893
Howdy!

389
00:34:39,632 --> 00:34:42,477
- Finally home.
- I'm so glad, Bob.

390
00:34:42,639 --> 00:34:45,193
I'm in that room too, Bob.
Don't mess with my things.

391
00:34:45,359 --> 00:34:47,301
All right, Grandpa.

392
00:34:52,877 --> 00:34:58,246
"July 9th. Diligence, tact,
and a keen sense of responsibility...

393
00:34:58,413 --> 00:35:02,636
...capacity for detail are your dominant
traits. Your sense of duty's strong."

394
00:35:45,130 --> 00:35:46,690
How long you been there?

395
00:35:46,858 --> 00:35:49,639
Just now arrived. Did I miss much?

396
00:35:51,305 --> 00:35:54,599
Not unless you never seen a man
wash his dirty carcass before.

397
00:35:54,855 --> 00:35:58,119
Boy, you got a big old pecker
for being such a little squirrel.

398
00:35:58,280 --> 00:36:00,188
That what you come here to see, Dick?

399
00:36:02,025 --> 00:36:03,430
No.

400
00:36:04,359 --> 00:36:07,622
Your brother said that Jesse
kept you in Kansas City some extra days.

401
00:36:07,784 --> 00:36:08,797
What was the reason?

402
00:36:10,919 --> 00:36:14,659
Well, I'm not at liberty to say exactly.

403
00:36:15,046 --> 00:36:20,349
Let me ask you this. Did Jesse mention
that me and Cummins were in cahoots?

404
00:36:21,477 --> 00:36:22,589
Is that so?

405
00:36:22,758 --> 00:36:26,532
Oh, dear. I went on and said too much,
have I?

406
00:36:26,885 --> 00:36:28,860
Well, who else is partners with you two?

407
00:36:31,140 --> 00:36:35,449
See, he'll cut our throats if he finds out.
You don't know him like I do.

408
00:36:35,619 --> 00:36:39,450
You do Jesse dirt,
you connive behind his back...

409
00:36:39,619 --> 00:36:42,302
...boy, he'll come after you
with a cleaver.

410
00:36:44,898 --> 00:36:47,290
So, what are you two cahoots
cooking up?

411
00:36:50,178 --> 00:36:51,740
Don't know that I should say.

412
00:36:52,867 --> 00:36:54,875
I'm not gonna wheedle
the dang news from you.

413
00:36:55,045 --> 00:36:56,733
How about we'll leave it a mystery...

414
00:36:56,993 --> 00:37:01,019
...and then we won't neither one of us
regret our little chat?

415
00:37:06,497 --> 00:37:09,149
Can you hand me that six-gun there, Bob?

416
00:37:17,856 --> 00:37:21,816
If you so much as mention my name
to Jesse...

417
00:37:21,984 --> 00:37:24,221
...boy, I'll find out about it.

418
00:37:24,382 --> 00:37:27,253
You had better believe that.

419
00:37:27,423 --> 00:37:29,365
And I'll look you up.

420
00:37:29,537 --> 00:37:34,237
I'll knock on your door,
and I will be as mad as a hornet.

421
00:37:34,943 --> 00:37:37,014
I will be hot.

422
00:37:38,847 --> 00:37:41,498
You be careful with that iron, Dick.

423
00:37:49,471 --> 00:37:52,918
You know where I stand on these matters
and that's all there is to it.

424
00:37:53,085 --> 00:37:56,533
Me and you can be as friendly as pigs
from now on.

425
00:38:20,987 --> 00:38:24,302
I'm Bunny Ford, stick your hands
up in the air!

426
00:38:24,475 --> 00:38:26,099
Mister.

427
00:38:31,162 --> 00:38:33,301
Oh, you have some nerve.

428
00:38:34,554 --> 00:38:39,735
We were just reading about the James boys
among the Mexicans.

429
00:38:41,400 --> 00:38:43,953
What's this? This ain't Jesse.

430
00:38:44,119 --> 00:38:47,121
- You don't know that.
- He would've never wore no mustache.

431
00:38:47,289 --> 00:38:49,556
Never was anywheres near a cannon.

432
00:38:49,719 --> 00:38:52,053
Let me see that picture.

433
00:38:52,215 --> 00:38:54,832
Boy, I can't even calculate
what I'm looking at.

434
00:38:55,062 --> 00:38:57,102
- Give me that.
- Ever since he was a child...

435
00:38:57,271 --> 00:39:00,337
...Bob's collected whatsoever he could find
about the James brothers.

436
00:39:00,503 --> 00:39:02,609
Yeah, got himself a little museum
in his room.

437
00:39:02,776 --> 00:39:06,223
Next time you come snooping around,
you better strap on a shooting iron!

438
00:39:06,743 --> 00:39:09,131
Well, you can see how scared I am.

439
00:39:09,301 --> 00:39:13,012
You too, Wood Hite. Cross me again,
I'll put a bullet through your head!

440
00:39:13,973 --> 00:39:15,120
Boy, you...

441
00:39:15,767 --> 00:39:18,318
Son, you better recollect
who my cousin is...

442
00:39:18,484 --> 00:39:22,378
...because you've seemed to misremembered
that Jesse loves me like the Good Book.

443
00:39:22,547 --> 00:39:26,028
Now, you may play it like you're
a dangerous person in the grocery store...

444
00:39:26,196 --> 00:39:28,499
...but don't misremember
who you be accounting to...

445
00:39:28,660 --> 00:39:30,994
...if I so much get my feelings hurt.
- I don't care!

446
00:39:31,156 --> 00:39:32,651
Do I have to yell "suwee"?

447
00:39:32,821 --> 00:39:34,707
Why don't we make up,
be pleasant for once?

448
00:39:34,868 --> 00:39:37,584
Why don't we pass the evening
like pleasant human beings?

449
00:39:37,747 --> 00:39:39,917
I like your nickel suit, cowboy.

450
00:40:04,689 --> 00:40:06,379
You see something?

451
00:40:07,568 --> 00:40:09,292
Just a bird.

452
00:40:12,912 --> 00:40:14,732
The month of October came...

453
00:40:14,895 --> 00:40:18,190
...and Jesse began seeing
Pinkerton operatives in every floor walker...

454
00:40:18,352 --> 00:40:22,575
...street sweeper, and common man
poking about in a store.

455
00:40:24,750 --> 00:40:27,172
On the morning of the 11 th,
he would wake his wife...

456
00:40:27,342 --> 00:40:31,369
...with the Scripture pertaining to
the Holy Family's flight into Egypt.

457
00:40:34,958 --> 00:40:39,660
Overnight, the Thomas Howard clan
vanished from Kansas City.

458
00:40:49,708 --> 00:40:52,261
Shortly thereafter,
four of the Blue Cut train robbers...

459
00:40:52,428 --> 00:40:55,144
...were arrested in shacks near Glendale.

460
00:40:59,980 --> 00:41:03,525
How Jesse could have known
remains a mystery.

461
00:41:15,082 --> 00:41:17,952
Theirs was a wandering existence.

462
00:41:18,124 --> 00:41:19,748
Men who choose to be outlaws...

463
00:41:19,913 --> 00:41:23,690
...cannot afford to remain in one place
for very long.

464
00:41:32,362 --> 00:41:36,451
- Well, goodness. Maybe I'll change my mind.
- Let's go. Let's go. Let's go.

465
00:41:36,617 --> 00:41:38,754
- Martha.
- Buck up, man.

466
00:41:38,920 --> 00:41:42,334
Wood and Dick would bicker
across the entire state of Kentucky...

467
00:41:42,503 --> 00:41:47,260
...until they made Russellville, home
of Major George Hite, Wood's father...

468
00:41:47,432 --> 00:41:50,432
...and uncle to Frank and Jesse James.

469
00:41:58,181 --> 00:42:00,254
You stay away from this one.

470
00:42:00,997 --> 00:42:02,939
She's my daddy's wife.

471
00:42:03,845 --> 00:42:05,122
You got it?

472
00:42:28,068 --> 00:42:29,628
Did you cook this, ma'am?

473
00:42:32,803 --> 00:42:34,973
I've got a nigger woman.

474
00:42:36,996 --> 00:42:37,976
How's that?

475
00:42:42,243 --> 00:42:45,470
Dick asked if I cooked this.

476
00:42:45,699 --> 00:42:47,127
Did you?

477
00:42:49,600 --> 00:42:50,583
No.

478
00:42:59,425 --> 00:43:01,759
She knew what he was like
when she married him.

479
00:43:27,199 --> 00:43:31,256
I guess we're the night owls, you and I.

480
00:43:32,605 --> 00:43:34,361
I'm glad.

481
00:43:36,573 --> 00:43:37,947
How come?

482
00:43:38,909 --> 00:43:41,397
You're interesting to look at.

483
00:43:42,268 --> 00:43:45,617
You have a real pleasant disposition.

484
00:43:47,197 --> 00:43:50,969
And I don't know, you sort of
make me feel warm all over.

485
00:43:52,891 --> 00:43:57,364
You know, I'm what they call a...
An inamorato.

486
00:44:01,081 --> 00:44:05,588
