549
00:51:28,272 --> 00:51:31,142
- I just happened by, Ed.
- Suppose you heard gossip, though.

550
00:51:31,312 --> 00:51:34,126
Suppose you heard Jim Cummins
come by, you might have thought...

551
00:51:34,288 --> 00:51:39,044
...that we were planning to capture you
or get that reward, and that ain't true.

552
00:51:39,215 --> 00:51:41,420
But you might have suspected it.

553
00:51:59,022 --> 00:52:01,509
Haven't heard a lick of gossip lately.

554
00:52:01,677 --> 00:52:05,931
I got 600 dollars stashed away.
I don't need no governor's reward.

555
00:52:08,717 --> 00:52:10,572
Well, it's the principle too.

556
00:52:15,372 --> 00:52:16,800
Well...

557
00:52:17,098 --> 00:52:20,447
- I'm glad I stopped by.
- Oh, me too.

558
00:52:44,232 --> 00:52:47,168
What do you say
if we were to go for a ride?

559
00:52:51,914 --> 00:52:54,662
We can go into town. I'll buy you dinner.

560
00:52:56,201 --> 00:52:58,403
Then I'll be on my way.

561
00:53:07,014 --> 00:53:08,672
Okay.

562
00:54:06,626 --> 00:54:08,284
You ready to go for a ride?

563
00:54:23,423 --> 00:54:25,693
We going to your place?

564
00:54:30,336 --> 00:54:32,375
You seen Ed Miller lately?

565
00:54:33,695 --> 00:54:35,733
Nobody has.

566
00:54:39,391 --> 00:54:41,878
Must have gone off to California.

567
00:54:45,759 --> 00:54:47,994
I'd still like to know where we're going.

568
00:54:52,957 --> 00:54:56,698
If you were going to see Jim Cummins,
wouldn't you follow this road?

569
00:55:01,915 --> 00:55:03,674
I guess so.

570
00:55:44,856 --> 00:55:46,263
Howdy.

571
00:55:56,696 --> 00:55:58,736
Oh, are you friends of my pa's?

572
00:56:03,606 --> 00:56:05,362
We're friends of Jim Cummins.

573
00:56:09,334 --> 00:56:12,115
Well, it so happens
he's been gone since August.

574
00:56:12,278 --> 00:56:14,253
And never said where he gone to.

575
00:56:18,966 --> 00:56:22,064
- I'm Matt Collins.
- Albert Ford.

576
00:56:22,230 --> 00:56:24,116
Very happy to meet you.

577
00:56:29,588 --> 00:56:32,937
- Dick Turpin.
- Pleased to make your acquaintance.

578
00:56:45,139 --> 00:56:47,047
I don't know where he is!
Leave me alone!

579
00:56:47,218 --> 00:56:48,910
Shut your mouth!
You shut your mouth!

580
00:56:50,802 --> 00:56:53,551
- You shut your mouth.
- I don't know where he is!

581
00:56:54,225 --> 00:56:56,168
- I don't know!
- Get in there.

582
00:56:57,008 --> 00:56:57,993
Shut up.

583
00:56:58,161 --> 00:57:00,549
- I don't know where he is!
- Shut up.

584
00:57:01,584 --> 00:57:02,991
- I don't know!
- Shut up.

585
00:57:03,152 --> 00:57:04,168
- Jesus.
- Shut up.

586
00:57:04,337 --> 00:57:06,344
Jesse, he's just a kid.

587
00:57:06,738 --> 00:57:10,250
He knows where his uncle Jim is and
that's gonna make him old soon enough.

588
00:57:10,417 --> 00:57:12,619
- Maybe he doesn't know.
- He knows!

589
00:57:12,784 --> 00:57:14,376
You need to ask and ask sometimes.

590
00:57:14,544 --> 00:57:18,024
Sometimes a child don't remember so much
at first. But it'll come back to him.

591
00:57:19,983 --> 00:57:22,404
My goodness, she's about to rip off,
sweetie.

592
00:57:22,575 --> 00:57:24,485
Just a little more here to get her started.

593
00:57:24,655 --> 00:57:27,306
Then I think I can rip her off
like a page from a book.

594
00:57:27,469 --> 00:57:29,477
Jesus, he can't even talk.

595
00:57:32,207 --> 00:57:33,700
Where's Jim?

596
00:57:33,870 --> 00:57:35,276
Where's Jim?

597
00:57:35,438 --> 00:57:37,325
Where's Jim? Where's Jim?

598
00:57:37,486 --> 00:57:40,716
Where's Jim? Where's Jim? Where's Jim?

599
00:57:41,038 --> 00:57:43,208
- Where's Jim?
- Quit it!

600
00:57:43,692 --> 00:57:45,995
You bastard! I don't know where he is!

601
00:57:46,156 --> 00:57:48,905
You won't believe me!
You never even gave me a chance!

602
00:57:49,067 --> 00:57:50,979
You kept my... You kept my mouth shut!

603
00:57:52,300 --> 00:57:55,562
I never know where Jim is or
when he comes! So leave me alone.

604
00:57:55,724 --> 00:57:58,057
Get off me, you son of a bitch!

605
00:58:48,935 --> 00:58:50,790
I'm worn out.

606
00:58:51,015 --> 00:58:53,763
I can't. No, see...

607
00:58:56,679 --> 00:58:59,133
My mind's all tangled anyway.

608
00:58:59,655 --> 00:59:02,970
Little deals like this
just make me feel dirty.

609
00:59:23,173 --> 00:59:25,115
Are you all right, Jesse?

610
00:59:52,514 --> 00:59:54,270
Jesse was sick...

611
00:59:54,433 --> 00:59:58,711
